quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  43,88,"(And Allâh has the knowledge) of (Prophet Muhammad’s) saying: "
  43,89,"So turn away from them (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم), and say: Salâm (peace)! But they will come to know.{1}",footnotes:1:[{43:89} The provision of this Verse was abrogated by the revelation of the Verse of fighting them {9:5}.]
  50,13,"And ‘Âd, and Fir‘aun (Pharaoh), and the brethren of Lût (Lot);"
  50,14,"And the Dwellers of the Wood, and the people of Tubba‘. Everyone of them denied (their) Messengers, so My Threat took effect."
  50,15,"Were We then tired with the first creation? Nay, they are in confused doubt about a new creation (i.e. Resurrection)."
  51,7,"By the heaven full of paths,"
  51,8,"Certainly, you have different ideas (about Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم and the Qur’ân)."
  51,9,"Turned aside therefrom (i.e. from Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم and the Qur’ân) is he who is turned aside (by the Decree and Preordainment القضاء والقدر of Allâh)."